---
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" class="legal-html">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Terms for using ExamDraft: permitted use, upload responsibility, Bring Your Own Key, and service limitations."
    />
    <title>Terms — ExamDraft</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  </head>
  <body class="legal-body overflow-x-hidden">
    <div class="legal-shell">
      <header class="legal-topbar sticky top-0 z-50">
        <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-5xl items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 sm:px-6">
          <a href="/en" class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 32 32" class="h-9 w-9 shrink-0">
              <rect width="32" height="32" rx="7" fill="#111111"/>
              <rect x="8" y="8" width="16" height="3.5" rx="1.75" fill="#f0ebe2"/>
              <rect x="8" y="14.25" width="11" height="3.5" rx="1.75" fill="#f0ebe2"/>
              <rect x="8" y="20.5" width="16" height="3.5" rx="1.75" fill="#f0ebe2"/>
            </svg>
            <div>
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-tight text-[#111318]">ExamDraft</p>
              <p class="text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[#707070]">Terms</p>
            </div>
          </a>

          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <a href="/terms" class="secondary-link px-4 py-2 text-xs">DE</a>
            <span class="study-accent rounded-full px-3 py-2 text-xs font-semibold">EN</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <main class="px-5 pb-20 pt-14 sm:px-6 sm:pt-16">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl space-y-8">
          <section class="legal-hero rounded-[2rem] px-6 py-8 sm:px-8 sm:py-10">
            <p class="legal-kicker">Use framework</p>
            <h1 class="legal-section-title mt-4 text-4xl sm:text-5xl">Terms for using ExamDraft</h1>
            <p class="legal-copy mt-6 max-w-3xl text-base sm:text-lg">
              These terms govern the use of ExamDraft as a tool for analyzing past exams,
              generating practice exams, and evaluating answers with AI support. The main goal
              is clarity: what the product is for, what remains your responsibility as the user,
              and which limits naturally apply to an AI-based study tool.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              <span class="legal-meta-chip">Version: April 2026</span>
              <span class="legal-meta-chip">Bring Your Own Key</span>
              <span class="legal-meta-chip">Study use only</span>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
            <article class="legal-card rounded-[1.7rem] p-6">
              <p class="legal-kicker">Summary</p>
              <ul class="legal-list legal-copy mt-4 text-sm">
                <li>ExamDraft is intended for lawful personal exam preparation.</li>
                <li>You may only use materials you have the right to use.</li>
                <li>You use your own API key and bear the related model costs yourself.</li>
                <li>Generated content is study material, not an official answer key or guaranteed assessment.</li>
              </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="legal-card rounded-[1.7rem] p-6">
              <p class="legal-kicker">Contact</p>
              <div class="legal-copy mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm">
                <p>
                  Questions about these terms can be sent to
                  <a href="mailto:legal@examdraft.com"> legal@examdraft.com</a>.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Privacy-related questions belong to
                  <a href="mailto:privacy@examdraft.com"> privacy@examdraft.com</a>.
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-card rounded-[1.9rem] p-6 sm:p-8">
            <p class="legal-kicker">1. Purpose of the service</p>
            <div class="legal-copy mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm sm:text-[15px]">
              <p>
                ExamDraft is an AI-assisted study tool. It helps users turn past exams and
                optional lecture context into new practice exams, type-specific drills, and
                AI-assisted answer evaluation.
              </p>
              <p>
                ExamDraft is not intended to replace official exam regulations, deliver binding
                grading decisions, or provide guaranteed predictions of a real university exam.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-card rounded-[1.9rem] p-6 sm:p-8">
            <p class="legal-kicker">2. Permitted use</p>
            <div class="legal-copy mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm sm:text-[15px]">
              <p>You may only use ExamDraft for lawful purposes, especially:</p>
              <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>your own exam preparation,</li>
                <li>legitimate study and practice workflows,</li>
                <li>internal, non-abusive teaching or learning contexts.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>Use is not permitted where it:</p>
              <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>violates copyright, exam rules, confidentiality duties, or comparable restrictions,</li>
                <li>processes protected third-party materials without authorization,</li>
                <li>supports cheating, evasion, or misuse in real examinations,</li>
                <li>abuses technical infrastructure or external providers in an unlawful way.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-card rounded-[1.9rem] p-6 sm:p-8">
            <p class="legal-kicker">3. Your responsibility for uploads and content</p>
            <div class="legal-copy mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm sm:text-[15px]">
              <p>
                You are responsible for the past exams, model solutions, lecture slides, or topic
                summaries you provide to ExamDraft.
              </p>
              <ul class="legal-list">
                <li>You should only use content you own or are otherwise entitled to use.</li>
                <li>You should not upload content whose use is prohibited by copyright, contracts, or exam rules.</li>
                <li>If materials contain personal or confidential information, you must assess yourself whether their use is lawful and appropriate.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                ExamDraft does not perform legal pre-screening of uploads. Responsibility for the
                legality of the submitted materials remains with you.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
            <article class="legal-card rounded-[1.7rem] p-6">
              <p class="legal-kicker">4. Bring Your Own Key</p>
              <div class="legal-copy mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm">
                <p>
                  ExamDraft works with your own provider key. That means you choose the provider
                  and you bear the resulting API costs yourself.
                </p>
                <p>
                  ExamDraft does not provide bundled model credits, its own token quota, or a
                  flat-rate model usage plan.
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>

            <article class="legal-card rounded-[1.7rem] p-6">
              <p class="legal-kicker">5. Dependence on external providers</p>
              <div class="legal-copy mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm">
                <p>
                  Parts of the product depend on external AI providers. If those providers change
                  models, pricing, limits, or policies, that can also affect how ExamDraft behaves.
                </p>
              </div>
            </article>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-card rounded-[1.9rem] p-6 sm:p-8">
            <p class="legal-kicker">6. Quality, limitations, and liability</p>
            <div class="legal-copy mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm sm:text-[15px]">
              <p>
                AI-generated content can be inaccurate, incomplete, or poorly phrased. That applies
                to analysis results, generated tasks, sample solutions, hints, and AI grading.
              </p>
              <p>
                ExamDraft is therefore provided as a study tool “as is”. We do not guarantee that a
                generated exam perfectly matches the style of a future real exam or that AI grading
                matches the decision of a real examiner.
              </p>
              <p>
                To the extent permitted by law, liability for slight negligence is limited. Mandatory
                statutory liability, especially for intent, gross negligence, or non-waivable duties,
                remains unaffected.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-card rounded-[1.9rem] p-6 sm:p-8">
            <p class="legal-kicker">7. Changes and further development</p>
            <div class="legal-copy mt-4 space-y-4 text-sm sm:text-[15px]">
              <p>
                ExamDraft may evolve over time. That can include changes to the interface,
                supported models, indicative pricing text, export options, or available learning modes.
              </p>
              <p>
                If these terms change in a material way, the current version published on the
                website is the governing version.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
